<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD538B1FCEFFA9DFB70FAAC" box="[810,1205,1363,1389]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FCEFFA9DFB70FAAC" blockId="644.[810,1205,1363,1389]" box="[810,1205,1363,1389]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<heading id="D09A81B1EDD538B1FCEFFA9DFB70FAAC" bold="true" box="[810,1205,1363,1389]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FCEFFA9DFB70FAAC" authority="Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[810,1205,1363,1389]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FCEFFA9DFB70FAAC" bold="true" box="[810,1205,1363,1389]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FCEFFA9DFC7EFAAC" bold="true" box="[810,955,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Haplostatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEDD538B1FC07FA9DFB70FAAC" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[962,1205,1363,1389]" journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD538B1FCEFFA59FCBCF900" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FCEFFA59FCBCF900" blockId="644.[810,1452,1431,2070]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FCEFFA59FC58FA70" bold="true" box="[810,925,1431,1457]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body vermiform, cylindrical, without any metameric division. Urosome not demarcated from prosome, indistinctly 3-segmented. Anal somite tipped with pair of claws. Rostrum distinct, semicircular. Antennule as unsegmented lobe. Antenna 2-segmented. Antennae and vestigial mouthparts positioned within pre-oral cavity. Labrum distinct. Mouthparts absent or represented by 1 pair of small, bimerous lobes. Legs absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD538B1FC9AF904FBB6F8C4" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FC9AF904FBB6F8C4" blockId="644.[810,1452,1431,2070]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FC9AF904FC36F922" bold="true" box="[863,1011,1737,1764]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<typeStatus id="54D6887FEDD538B1FC9AF904FC5FF925" box="[863,922,1738,1764]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FBC4F907FCA7F8C4" authority="Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incubatrix">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FBC4F907FAC7F922" box="[1025,1282,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Haplostatus incubatrix</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEDD538B1FACCF907FCA7F8C4" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD538B0FC9AF8C0FD13F8C7" lastPageId="645" lastPageNumber="646" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B0FC9AF8C0FD13F8C7" blockId="644.[810,1452,1431,2070]" lastBlockId="645.[136,778,1738,1798]" lastPageId="645" lastPageNumber="646" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FC9AF8C0FC09F8E9" bold="true" box="[863,972,1806,1832]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Remarks</emphasis>
. The discovery of a second species enables us to better define the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FBA8F8FEFB31F88B" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[1133,1268,1840,1866]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FBA8F8FEFB31F88B" box="[1133,1268,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Haplostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In both species the urosome is segmented and carries a pair of claws posteriorly on the anal somite, and the antennae and mouthparts are located within a pre-oral cavity. These are the major diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FB21F876FAAEF813" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[1252,1387,1976,2002]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FB21F876FAAEF813" box="[1252,1387,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Haplostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FCB8F814FBCEF835" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[893,1035,2010,2036]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Pholeterides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FCB8F814FBCEF835" box="[893,1035,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Pholeterides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FB80F814FB12F835" authorityName="Lafargue &amp; Laubier" authorityYear="1968" box="[1093,1239,2010,2036]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Sicyodelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FB80F814FB12F835" box="[1093,1239,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Sicyodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described as possessing a 3- or 4-segmented urosome, terminating in a pair of claws on the anal somite, as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD438B0FD95F904FD12F925" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[592,727,1738,1764]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="645" pageNumber="646" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD438B0FD95F904FD12F925" box="[592,727,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="645" pageNumber="646">Haplostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but these two genera both have legs, unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD438B0FD8DF922FD0AF8C7" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[584,719,1772,1798]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Haplostatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="645" pageNumber="646" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD438B0FD8DF922FD0AF8C7" box="[584,719,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="645" pageNumber="646">Haplostatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
